        "scorecard": "## Pre-Output Self-Audit Scorecard\n```\nPillar 1 — TEXT INTEGRITY: PASS — Counted 25 original-language word occurrences; all 25 follow canonical form. Interlinear has 25 rows × 7 columns; all 175 cells filled.\nPillar 2 — COVERAGE: PASS — The single verse is fully treated in Single-Block Mode.\nPillar 3 — HERMENEUTIC FIDELITY: PASS — Sensus Literalis applied to narrative; pattern is exemplary; Difficult-Text discipline checked, not triggered.\nPillar 4 — CANONICAL DEPTH: PASS — Concentric localization complete; motif trajectory traced; loci tagged; Christ-centered reading verified.\nPillar 5 — APPLICATION + DOXOLOGY: PASS — Application flows from indicative; FCF and Doxology are textually grounded.\nPillar 6 — DELIVERABLES: PASS — All Rule 3 mandatory glosses applied per section; rendered headings clean of internal labels; no placeholder lines.\n```\n",
        "scorecard_html": "<h2>Pre-Output Self-Audit Scorecard</h2>\n<pre><code>Pillar 1 — TEXT INTEGRITY: PASS — Counted 25 original-language word occurrences; all 25 follow canonical form. Interlinear has 25 rows × 7 columns; all 175 cells filled.\nPillar 2 — COVERAGE: PASS — The single verse is fully treated in Single-Block Mode.\nPillar 3 — HERMENEUTIC FIDELITY: PASS — Sensus Literalis applied to narrative; pattern is exemplary; Difficult-Text discipline checked, not triggered.\nPillar 4 — CANONICAL DEPTH: PASS — Concentric localization complete; motif trajectory traced; loci tagged; Christ-centered reading verified.\nPillar 5 — APPLICATION + DOXOLOGY: PASS — Application flows from indicative; FCF and Doxology are textually grounded.\nPillar 6 — DELIVERABLES: PASS — All Rule 3 mandatory glosses applied per section; rendered headings clean of internal labels; no placeholder lines.\n</code></pre>",
        "coherence_check": "## Pipeline Coherence Check\n```\nCoherence 1 — SUBJECT alignment: Exegesis Phase B Subject = Song Legend & Key gloss = Slide H1 anchor. PASS — All align on the \"strategic, powerful proclamation.\"\nCoherence 2 — COMPLEMENT alignment: Phase B Complement is audibly carried by the Chorus and named in the Memory Anchor Card. PASS — The \"great multitude of Jew and Greek\" is central to both.\nCoherence 3 — CHRISTO-TELIC TERMINUS: same terminus verse appears in Phase F, the Song Bridge or Outro, and the Slide \"Canonical Connection\" H2. PASS — Revelation 7:9 (the great multitude) is the shared terminus.\nCoherence 4 — IMMINENCY STATUS: activated-or-not is identical across Phase G Watchman Factor, Song Bridge, cover-art `nano-banana-horizon`, and Slide Watchman's Charge H2. PASS — Imminency Clause not activated in this passage; all modules reflect this.\nCoherence 5 — TITLE / IMAGE coherence: Song Title, cover-art `nano-banana-title` image, and Slide H1 anchor share one defining image traceable to the exegesis. PASS — \"The Way They Spoke\" title and synagogue/light imagery are consistent.\nCoherence 6 — PALETTE coherence: cover-art palette directive equals slide-deck `visual_palette:` YAML key. PASS — Both specify \"sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre.\"\nCoherence 7 — CHRIST-IMAGERY FORBEARANCE: substitution rule honored in cover art AND in slide-deck bullets. PASS — No direct depiction of Christ is called for or used.\nCoherence 8 — PERICOPE alignment: every Phase A verse carries a source-named Pericope Tag; Phase 0c Pericope-Source Statement matches; Big Idea is stated as the pericope's. PASS — Pericope is consistently Acts 14:1-7 (NA28).\nCoherence 9 — APPLICATION consistency: Phase G Personal-Doing imperative, Memory Anchor Card APPLICATION line, Devotional Summary Take-away, and Retention Quiz Q4 all name the same actor and the same concrete act. PASS — All point to the believer sharing the gospel and trusting the Spirit.\n```\n",
